{"questionId":"27797","questionHtml":"<p>For&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, find an expression for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to use the chain rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi></mrow><msqrt><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nb